<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="60" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1328,2037]" pageId="19" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,466,1868,1893]" pageId="19" pageNumber="60">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be separated from others in the group by having ovoid pronotal punctures which are relatively close together (between 1 and 1.5 puncture diameters along the minor axis) and the seta associated with each puncture being short.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
